    summary: "Rajavej Chiang Mai is a solid mid-tier private hospital that fills the gap between budget government hospitals and premium-chain facilities. Its 28-year operating history, 150+ beds, and comprehensive specialty roster make it a credible full-service option. The hospital's standout feature is genuine multilingual support — medical translators with clinical training in English, Japanese, Filipino, and Korean — making it a practical choice for non-Thai-speaking patients. Inpatient facilities are comfortable and well-appointed. It is noticeably cheaper than Bangkok Hospital Chiang Mai while providing comparable routine care. Best suited for expats seeking affordable private-hospital comfort with good English communication support.",
