    specialties: ["Cardiology & Cardiovascular Surgery", "Orthopedics & Bone Surgery", "Endocrinology & Diabetes", "Occupational Medicine", "Emergency & Trauma", "Obstetrics & High-Risk Pregnancy", "Intensive Care", "Cardio-Rehabilitation", "Minimally Invasive Surgery"],
    strengths: "Part of the BDMS (Bangkok Dusit Medical Services) network — Thailand's largest private hospital group — giving it access to shared clinical protocols, network referrals to Bangkok Hospital's main campus, and BDMS international insurance billing arrangements. 103-bed modern facility on Maliwan Road described as 'clean, professional and reasonably priced' by expat reviewers, with English-speaking doctors who proactively follow up with patients. Serves as a regional referral center for Northeastern Thailand, with particular specialist depth in cardiovascular care (cardiac catheterization, CTA Coronary Angiography, pacemakers, angioplasty). Equipped with modern 3D-camera minimally invasive surgery. HA Thailand accredited.",
    weaknesses: "With 103 beds, it is smaller than competitors Khon Kaen Ram and Srinagarind — specialist breadth is narrower and complex cases requiring advanced oncology or neurosurgery may need referral to Bangkok. Does not hold JCI accreditation (unlike some other BDMS branches), which may affect specific international insurer eligibility. English reviews are positive but limited in volume (285 Google reviews), suggesting it sees fewer international patients than might be expected.",
    summary: "Bangkok Hospital KhonKaen offers the reassurance of BDMS network membership with a modern, clean facility and genuinely English-friendly clinical staff in a compact 103-bed setting. Its cardiovascular program is a genuine strength for this size of hospital. It is an excellent choice for expats in Khon Kaen who value the BDMS network brand and billing infrastructure, direct insurance coordination, and good English communication — but those requiring complex surgical intervention or advanced oncology should plan for potential referral to Bangkok.",
