    strengths: "Established in 1992 and opened in 1995, Khon Kaen Ram is part of the Ramkhamhaeng Hospital Group and has grown into one of the largest private hospitals in Northeastern Thailand with approximately 300 beds. Clinically strong with genuine depth in cardiology (cardiac catheterization and angioplasty), oncology (radiation therapy and chemotherapy), and ophthalmology (it introduced ReLEX SMILE laser eye surgery to the northeast). First hospital in the northeast to offer CT scanning services and early adopter of MRI. Has a dedicated spa and sports complex, hemodialysis center, and an international customer email contact. Holds HA Thailand accreditation.",
    weaknesses: "Does not hold JCI accreditation, which may complicate claims with some international insurers. International patient infrastructure is limited — English-speaking services are available but not as structured or prominent as BDMS network competitors. Some patient reviews mention that foreign insurance coverage is not guaranteed, requiring case-by-case insurer coordination. A single negative review noted nursing staff professionalism concerns.",
