    specialties: ["Cardiology & Queen Sirikit Heart Center", "Oncology & Cancer Center", "Neurology & Neurosurgery", "Organ Transplantation", "Gastroenterology & Liver Disease", "Orthopedics", "Obstetrics & Gynecology", "Pediatrics & Neonatology", "Nephrology & Dialysis", "Endocrinology & Diabetes (Center of Excellence)", "Ophthalmology", "Rehabilitation", "Emergency & Super-Tertiary Trauma"],
    strengths: "The undisputed medical powerhouse of Northeast Thailand and one of Thailand's finest teaching hospitals. With 1,466+ beds and over 1 million patients per year, Srinagarind is designated as a 'super tertiary care' hospital and serves as the ultimate final referral center for complicated and rare diseases throughout Northeastern Thailand. Ranked Thailand's best hospital by Newsweek in 2021. Awarded the Advanced Healthcare Accreditation (A-HA) by Thailand's HAI — the highest national accreditation tier — valid 2025-2029. The Queen Sirikit Heart Center of the Northeast holds its own JCI accreditation (renewed 2024). Established KKU Center of Excellence for Diabetes and an internationally recognized cancer research and clinical trials network (ATLAS Asia). Significantly lower cost than private hospitals — extraordinary value for the quality of specialist care available.",
    weaknesses: "As a major public university teaching hospital, waiting times can be very long — forum accounts report multi-hour waits as standard. International patient services, while available (English-speaking coordinators, visa assistance), are less polished and less proactively managed than at private hospitals. The environment is busier and more institutional than private competitors. English fluency among front-line nursing and administrative staff is more variable than at private facilities.",
    summary: "Srinagarind Hospital is a world-class academic medical center that happens to be in Khon Kaen — not a compromise but a genuine best-in-region option for complex, serious medical conditions. For expatriates needing advanced cardiology (Queen Sirikit Heart Center), oncology, transplantation, neurosurgery, or any highly specialized referral care, Srinagarind offers quality and expertise that rivals Bangkok's top private hospitals at a fraction of the price. The trade-off is a public-hospital experience: long waits, a busier environment, and less seamless international patient hand-holding. Expats in good health or needing routine care may prefer the private hospitals in town, but should know Srinagarind is the region's top referral destination for serious illness.",
