    strengths: "Southern Thailand's most internationally accredited hospital, holding JCI, GHA (first in Songkhla province and all of BDMS), HA Thailand, and KAHF accreditations simultaneously. Named in Newsweek's World's Best Hospitals 2024. A 400-bed BDMS flagship facility with 70+ full-time specialists and 100 consulting physicians, serving patients from Malaysia, Singapore, and Indonesia as well as the local expat community. Dedicated International Patient Advocate Program (IPAP) with multilingual coordinators fluent in English, Thai, and Bahasa Melayu — crucial for the large Malaysian patient base. Helicopter landing pad, 64-slice cardiac CT, MRI, 3D ultrasound, and full trauma capabilities. Muslim-friendly (prayer room, halal food). Heart Center, Cancer Center, and Brain & Spine Center are key draws.",
