    summary: "Bangkok Hospital Hat Yai is the dominant international-standard hospital for southern Thailand and one of the most accredited in the country, with JCI, GHA, HA Thailand, and KAHF credentials alongside Newsweek's World's Best Hospital 2024 recognition. It serves as the primary destination for cross-border medical tourism from Malaysia and Singapore, with dedicated multilingual advocacy, halal services, and structured pre-arrival support. The 400-bed BDMS facility brings world-class cardiac, cancer, and neurological care to Hat Yai. For expats and health insurance clients in the South, this is the go-to private hospital — though its premium pricing reflects its status.",
