    valueForMoney: 10,
    specialties: ["Naradhiwas Rajanagarindra Heart Center", "NKC Institute of Gastroenterology & Hepatology", "Cancer Center (Radiation Oncology since 1982)", "Trauma Center", "Neurology & Neurosurgery", "Nephrology", "Hematology", "Orthopedics", "Bariatric Surgery (Center of Excellence)", "Pediatrics", "Obstetrics & Gynecology", "Internal Medicine", "Psychiatry", "Palliative Care", "Organ Transplantation"],
    strengths: "The #1 ranked regional hospital in Thailand (Newsweek/Statista 2024, outside Bangkok), affiliated with Prince of Songkla University — Thailand's top southern university. Super-tertiary referral center with 855 beds and 23 operating rooms serving 13 surgical specialties. Performs 12,000+ elective surgeries annually. Six dedicated centers including the Heart Center, NKC Gastroenterology Institute, and Cancer Center (operating since 1982 with dual-energy CT precision radiotherapy). Center of Excellence in Bariatric Surgery. Faculty of Medicine teaching hospital with internationally trained academic physicians. Dramatically lower cost than Bangkok Hospital Hat Yai — cardiac procedures at roughly 60-70% less than US/UK equivalents. Academic physicians are often frontier specialists in their fields. Serves patients from Malaysia, Singapore, and the entire Deep South.",
    weaknesses: "As a government university hospital, bureaucratic processes and crowding create long wait times for non-emergency outpatient appointments. English language proficiency is inconsistent — available from some academic physicians but unreliable at administrative and nursing levels. International billing coordination, insurance direct-billing, and pre-arrival planning support lag far behind Bangkok Hospital Hat Yai. No JCI accreditation. No dedicated international patient program. Medical tourism infrastructure is minimal. Facilities, while technically capable, lack the hotel-like comfort of private hospitals.",
    summary: "Songklanagarind Hospital is arguably the finest academic medical institution in southern Thailand and ranks #1 among Thailand's regional hospitals. As the teaching hospital of Prince of Songkla University, it houses specialist physicians of outstanding calibre — many internationally trained — and operates at super-tertiary level, taking the most complex referrals from across the South. Its Heart Center, Gastroenterology Institute, and Cancer Center are genuine centers of excellence. For expats and insurance clients willing to navigate a busy government-hospital environment, the quality of care per baht spent is unmatched in the region. However, those needing seamless English support, insurance direct-billing, or luxury inpatient comfort should consider Bangkok Hospital Hat Yai as the primary option, using Songklanagarind for specialist referrals.",
